# ERP Multi-Agent Core Rules

Authoritative domain source is [`docs/ERP-Systembeschreibung.md`](../../docs/ERP-Systembeschreibung.md) (konsolidiert v2.0; Abschnitte 1–17 entsprechen der historischen v1.3-Struktur). Archivierte Einzelstände: `docs/_archiv/systembeschreibung-und-phasen-legacy/`. Repository-Orientierung für Agenten: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md). PWA/UI-Link-Hub: [`docs/referenz-ui-ux.md`](../../docs/referenz-ui-ux.md).

Non-negotiable rules:
- Do not simplify domain logic.
- Enforce strict tenant isolation.
- Use versioning for business-critical states; no destructive overwrite.
- Preserve end-to-end traceability: invoice -> measurement -> LV -> offer -> project -> customer.
- Never mix immutable system text with editable business text.
- When uncertain, state assumptions explicitly and request clarification.

Delivery rules:
- Work in phases with explicit quality gates.
- Before merging to `main` / `master`: green GitHub Actions job **`backend`** (see `.github/workflows/ci.yml`); follow `.github/pull_request_template.md` and QA §5a in `docs/contracts/qa-fin-0-gate-readiness.md`. Branch protection: `docs/runbooks/github-branch-protection-backend.md`.
- For production go-live on invoicing / tax / e-invoice topics: use the non-code checklist [`Checklisten/compliance-rechnung-finanz.md`](../../Checklisten/compliance-rechnung-finanz.md) with tax counsel / DPO / PL — it does not replace legal advice or the README’s separate release GO for GoBD/compliance.
- Do not commit secrets (env files with credentials, private SSH keys, tokens); canonical Git remote is the team repo `rhermann90/ERP` (see root `README.md`).
- Every output must include: result, rationale, risks, open questions.
- Explain impact on legal compliance, data consistency, maintainability, and PWA readiness.
- For purely mechanical, non-domain edits (e.g. spelling in unrelated comments, agent-doc link fixes): keep result and rationale concise; for risks, compliance, data consistency, maintainability, and PWA readiness, state explicitly when none apply (a short phrase or “none” per dimension is enough). For anything touching domain logic, API contracts, persistence, auth, or finance/tax UI, use the full format without exception.
- Prefer scalable, modular, and testable solutions over quick hacks.

Cursor Plan mode (IDE):
- Whenever the session is in **Plan mode** (collaborative planning), **every** assistant turn that lays out or updates a plan must use the **TodoWrite** tool: concrete, executable items with stable `id` values, sensible `status` (`pending`, `in_progress`, `completed`, `cancelled` as appropriate). Prose or markdown-only checklists do **not** replace tool todos when the todo tool is available; narrative text supplements the todo list.

Review rules:
- Treat missing tests for critical paths as incomplete.
- Flag legal/financial risks early.
- Stop phase progression on unresolved critical findings.
